    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Mosiah",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 15,
        "summary": "How Christ is both the Father and the Son\u2014He will make intercession and bear the transgressions of His people\u2014They and all the holy prophets are His seed\u2014He brings to pass the Resurrection\u2014Little children have eternal life. About 148\u00a0B.C.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "And now Abinadi said unto them: I would that ye should understand that God himself shall come down among the children of men, and shall redeem his people.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 54:5; 1\u00a0Tim. 3:16; Mosiah 13:34 (33\u201334).",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 74
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Manifestations of.",
                        "start": 89,
                        "end": 93
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Mission of.",
                        "start": 136,
                        "end": 142
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And because he dwelleth in flesh he shall be called the Son of God, and having subjected the flesh to the will of the Father, being the Father and the Son\u2014",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 3:5; 7:27; Alma 7:9 (9\u201313).",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Condescension of.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 19:7. TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Divine Sonship.",
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 66
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Will of.",
                        "start": 106,
                        "end": 110
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 9:6; 64:8; John 10:30; 14:10 (8\u201310); Mosiah 5:7; Alma 11:39 (38\u201339); Ether 3:14.",
                        "start": 118,
                        "end": 124
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The Father, because he was conceived by the power of God; and the Son, because of the flesh; thus becoming the Father and Son\u2014",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 93:4.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 1:32 (31\u201333); Mosiah 3:8 (8\u20139); Alma 7:10; 3\u00a0Ne. 1:14. TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Divine Sonship.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 36
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And they are one God, yea, the very Eternal Father of heaven and of earth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 6:4. TG\u00a0Godhead.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 11:39.",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 43
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 3:8; Hel. 14:12; 3\u00a0Ne. 9:15; Ether 4:7.",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 50
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And thus the flesh becoming subject to the Spirit, or the Son to the Father, being one God, suffereth temptation, and yieldeth not to the temptation, but suffereth himself to be mocked, and scourged, and cast out, and disowned by his people.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 4:2; Heb. 4:15. TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Temptation of.",
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 101
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 19:1.",
                        "start": 190,
                        "end": 198
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 21:42; Mark 8:31; Luke 17:25; 23:38.",
                        "start": 234,
                        "end": 240
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And after all this, after working many mighty miracles among the children of men, he shall be led, yea, even as Isaiah said, as a sheep before the shearer is dumb, so he opened not his mouth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 53:7.",
                        "start": 109,
                        "end": 111
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 23:9; John 19:9 (9\u201310); Mosiah 14:7. TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Trials of.",
                        "start": 170,
                        "end": 176
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Yea, even so he shall be led, crucified, and slain, the flesh becoming subject even unto death, the will of the Son being swallowed up in the will of the Father.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Crucifixion of.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 39
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 53:10.",
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 61
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 22:42; John 6:38; 3\u00a0Ne. 11:11.",
                        "start": 100,
                        "end": 104
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
                        "data-pointer-type": "media",
                        "data-scroll-id": "p7",
                        "title": "Associated Content"
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And thus God breaketh the bands of death, having gained the victory over death; giving the Son power to make intercession for the children of men\u2014",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 5:7.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hosea 13:14; 1\u00a0Cor. 15:57 (55\u201357); Mosiah 16:7.",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 67
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 2:9; Mosiah 14:12; Moro. 7:28 (27\u201328).",
                        "start": 109,
                        "end": 121
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Having ascended into heaven, having the bowels of mercy; being filled with compassion towards the children of men; standing betwixt them and justice; having broken the bands of death, taken upon himself their iniquity and their transgressions, having redeemed them, and satisfied the demands of justice.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 14:5 (5\u201312). TG\u00a0Self-Sacrifice.",
                        "start": 195,
                        "end": 202
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Mission of.",
                        "start": 270,
                        "end": 279
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And now I say unto you, who shall declare his generation? Behold, I say unto you, that when his soul has been made an offering for sin he shall see his seed. And now what say ye? And who shall be his seed?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 53:8.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 56
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Lev. 6:25 (25\u201326).",
                        "start": 131,
                        "end": 134
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 53:10; Mosiah 5:7; 27:25; Moro. 7:19. TG\u00a0God the Father, Jehovah.",
                        "start": 152,
                        "end": 156
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold I say unto you, that whosoever has heard the words of the prophets, yea, all the holy prophets who have prophesied concerning the coming of the Lord\u2014I say unto you, that all those who have hearkened unto their words, and believed that the Lord would redeem his people, and have looked forward to that day for a remission of their sins, I say unto you, that these are his seed, or they are the heirs of the kingdom of God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 10:16; D&C 84:36 (36\u201338).",
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 73
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Kingdom of God, in Heaven; Kingdom of God, on Earth.",
                        "start": 413,
                        "end": 420
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For these are they whose sins he has borne; these are they for whom he has died, to redeem them from their transgressions. And now, are they not his seed?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 14:12; Alma 7:13; 11:40 (40\u201341).",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 32
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Yea, and are not the prophets, every one that has opened his mouth to prophesy, that has not fallen into transgression, I mean all the holy prophets ever since the world began? I say unto you that they are his seed.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Zech. 7:12; Matt. 11:13; 1\u00a0Ne. 3:20. TG\u00a0Sons and Daughters of God.",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 29
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And these are they who have published peace, who have brought good tidings of good, who have published salvation; and said unto Zion: Thy God reigneth!",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 12:21 (21\u201324); 27:37.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 52:7.",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 74
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Missionary Work.",
                        "start": 93,
                        "end": 102
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And O how beautiful upon the mountains were their feet!",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And again, how beautiful upon the mountains are the feet of those that are still publishing peace!",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And again, how beautiful upon the mountains are the feet of those who shall hereafter publish peace, yea, from this time henceforth and forever!",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And behold, I say unto you, this is not all. For O how beautiful upon the mountains are the feet of him that bringeth good tidings, that is the founder of peace, yea, even the Lord, who has redeemed his people; yea, him who has granted salvation unto his people;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Nahum 1:15; 3\u00a0Ne. 20:40; D&C 128:19.",
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 96
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Micah 5:5 (4\u20137); John 16:33. TG\u00a0Peace of God.",
                        "start": 155,
                        "end": 160
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For were it not for the redemption which he hath made for his people, which was prepared from the foundation of the world, I say unto you, were it not for this, all mankind must have perished.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 4:6.",
                        "start": 98,
                        "end": 108
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 9:7 (6\u201313).",
                        "start": 183,
                        "end": 191
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But behold, the bands of death shall be broken, and the Son reigneth, and hath power over the dead; therefore, he bringeth to pass the resurrection of the dead.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And there cometh a resurrection, even a first resurrection; yea, even a resurrection of those that have been, and who are, and who shall be, even until the resurrection of Christ\u2014for so shall he be called.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jacob 4:11; Alma 40:16 (16\u201321). TG\u00a0Firstfruits.",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And now, the resurrection of all the prophets, and all those that have believed in their words, or all those that have kept the commandments of God, shall come forth in the first resurrection; therefore, they are the first resurrection.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "They are raised to dwell with God who has redeemed them; thus they have eternal life through Christ, who has broken the bands of death.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 15:1 (1\u20135); 24:3 (3\u20134); 1\u00a0Ne. 15:33 (33\u201336); D&C 76:62 (50\u201370).",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Death, Power over.",
                        "start": 109,
                        "end": 115
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And these are those who have part in the first resurrection; and these are they that have died before Christ came, in their ignorance, not having salvation declared unto them. And thus the Lord bringeth about the restoration of these; and they have a part in the first resurrection, or have eternal life, being redeemed by the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 9:26 (25\u201326); D&C 137:7.",
                        "start": 146,
                        "end": 155
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And little children also have eternal life.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 29:46; 137:10. TG\u00a0Salvation of Little Children.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 19
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But behold, and fear, and tremble before God, for ye ought to tremble; for the Lord redeemeth none such that rebel against him and die in their sins; yea, even all those that have perished in their sins ever since the world began, that have wilfully rebelled against God, that have known the commandments of God, and would not keep them; these are they that have no part in the first resurrection.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 5:29; Jacob 6:9; 7:19.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Josh. 22:16; Job 24:13; Ps. 5:10; 1\u00a0Ne. 2:23 (21\u201324).",
                        "start": 109,
                        "end": 114
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 18:26; 1\u00a0Ne. 15:33 (32\u201333); Moro. 10:26.",
                        "start": 131,
                        "end": 134
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 40:19.",
                        "start": 338,
                        "end": 343
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 76:85.",
                        "start": 363,
                        "end": 365
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Telestial Glory.",
                        "start": 384,
                        "end": 396
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore ought ye not to tremble? For salvation cometh to none such; for the Lord hath redeemed none such; yea, neither can the Lord redeem such; for he cannot deny himself; for he cannot deny justice when it has its claim.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 12:32; 34:16 (15\u201316); 42:1.",
                        "start": 194,
                        "end": 201
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And now I say unto you that the time shall come that the salvation of the Lord shall be declared to every nation, kindred, tongue, and people.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 67:2 (1\u20132). TG\u00a0Missionary Work.",
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 66
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Yea, Lord, thy watchmen shall lift up their voice; with the voice together shall they sing; for they shall see eye to eye, when the Lord shall bring again Zion.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 52:8 (8\u201310); Mosiah 12:22 (22\u201324).",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Watchman.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 23
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 178
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Break forth into joy, sing together, ye waste places of Jerusalem; for the Lord hath comforted his people, he hath redeemed Jerusalem.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The Lord hath made bare his holy arm in the eyes of all the nations; and all the ends of the earth shall see the salvation of our God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Salvation.",
                        "start": 113,
                        "end": 122
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}